2026-05-17 18:34:45 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #6 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] execute_ideal({"code": "# intent: Load the radiocarbon and climate Excel files, identify Maltese Neolithic Homo sapiens samples, pick northernmost sample and tie-break by later calibrated year, convert its calendar year to BP, find climate rows with closest Age_ky (converted to years BP = Age_ky*1000) and return max Al among those rows rounded to 4 decimals.\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom math import isfinite\n\n# load radiocarbon\nrc_path = 'DOWNLOAD_PATHS[\"s3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-archeology-hard-1/files/radiocarbon_database_regional.xlsx\"]'\nclim_path = 'DOWNLOAD_PATHS[\"s3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-archeology-easy-4/files/climateMeasurements.xlsx\"]'\n\n# pandas read\nrc = pd.read_excel(rc_path, sheet_name=0)\nclim = pd.read_excel(clim_path, sheet_name=0, header=0)\n\nprint('radiocarbon rows:', len(rc))\nprint('climate rows:', len(clim))\n\n# normalize column names\nrc.columns = [c.strip() for c in rc.columns]\nclim.columns = [str(c).strip() for c in clim.columns]\n\n# filter Malta rows: Region or Site contains 'Malta' (case-insensitive)\nmalta_mask = rc['Region'].astype(str).str.contains('Malta', case=False, na=False) | rc['Site'].astype(str).str.contains('Malta', case=False, na=False)\nrc_malta = rc[malta_mask].copy()\nprint('malta rows:', len(rc_malta))\n\n# Filter Neolithic and Homo sapiens\nrc_malta = rc_malta[rc_malta['Culture'].astype(str).str.contains('Neolithic', case=False, na=False)]\nrc_malta = rc_malta[rc_malta['Species'].astype(str).str.contains('Homo sapiens', case=False, na=False)]\nprint('malta Neolithic Homo sapiens rows:', len(rc_malta))\n\n# If no rows by site/region, try Site contains 'Malta' differently\n\n# Parse Cal. BC 2 sigma if present, else 1 sigma. Columns may have two identical names; find columns by pattern\ncal_cols = [c for c in rc.columns if 'Cal. BC' in str(c)]\ncal_cols\n\n# choose Cal. BC 2 sigma if exists\ncal2 = None\nfor c in cal_cols:\n    if '2 sigma' in c:\n        cal2 = c\n        break\nif cal2 is None and len(cal_cols)>0:\n    cal2 = cal_cols[0]\n\nprint('using calendar column:', cal2)\n\n# function to get midpoint of a range like '6340-6294' or '6211-6011'\nimport re\n\ndef midpoint_range(val):\n    if not isinstance(val, str):\n        return None\n    # find all years as integers\n    nums = re.findall(r\"(\\d{3,4})\", val)\n    if len(nums)>=2:\n        a = int(nums[0])\n        b = int(nums[1])\n        return (a+b)/2.0\n    return None\n\nrc_malta['cal_mid'] = rc_malta[cal2].astype(str).apply(midpoint_range)\nprint(rc_malta[['Region','Site','Culture','Species','Latitude','Longitude', cal2, 'cal_mid']].head(20))\n\n# find northernmost (max Latitude). Convert Latitude to numeric\nrc_malta['Latitude'] = pd.to_numeric(rc_malta['Latitude'], errors='coerce')\nmax_lat = rc_malta['Latitude'].max()\ncandidates = rc_malta[rc_malta['Latitude']==max_lat].copy()\nprint('max latitude:', max_lat, 'candidates:', len(candidates))\n\nif len(candidates)>1:\n    # tie-break by later calendar year: later means smaller BC value, so larger cal_mid? Wait cal_mid is BC, so 'later' in calendar means numerically smaller BC.\n    # We treat cal_mid as BC; later year = smaller BC number. So pick row with minimal cal_mid.\n    candidates['cal_mid_num'] = pd.to_numeric(candidates['cal_mid'], errors='coerce')\n    # drop NA\n    candidates = candidates[candidates['cal_mid_num'].notna()]\n    cand = candidates.sort_values('cal_mid_num').iloc[0]\nelse:\n    cand = candidates.iloc[0]\n\nprint('chosen sample row:')\nprint(cand[['Region','Site','Latitude','cal_mid']])\n\n# Convert sample cal_mid BC to years BP. Assuming 'Cal. BC' means 'years before AD 0'? BP convention: 1950. If Cal. BC 6000 -> BP = 6000 + 1950? But gold chain said compute sample calendar year as midpoint of calibrated BC range and then use climate Age_ky * 1000 as years before present. The chain uses direct comparison between BC and Age_ky*1000; must convert BC to years BP by adding 1950.\n# We'll convert cal_mid BC to years before present (BP) by: BP = cal_mid + 1950\ncal_mid = cand['cal_mid']\nsample_BP = None\nif pd.notna(cal_mid):\n    sample_BP = float(cal_mid) + 1950.0\n\nprint('sample cal_mid (BC):', cal_mid, 'sample BP:', sample_BP)\n\n# climate Age_ky convert to years BP: Age_ky * 1000 + 0? The sheet likely uses Age_ky as thousand years before present; so BP = Age_ky*1000\nclim_age_col = None\nfor c in clim.columns:\n    if 'Age_ky' in c:\n        clim_age_col = c\n        break\nprint('climate age col:', clim_age_col)\n\nclim = clim[clim[clim_age_col].notna()].copy()\nclim['Age_ky_num'] = pd.to_numeric(clim[clim_age_col], errors='coerce')\nclim = clim[clim['Age_ky_num'].notna()].copy()\nclim['Age_BP'] = clim['Age_ky_num'] * 1000.0\n\n# compute absolute difference to sample_BP\nclim['diff'] = (clim['Age_BP'] - sample_BP).abs()\nmin_diff = clim['diff'].min()\nclosest = clim[clim['diff']==min_diff]\nprint('min diff years:', min_diff, 'closest rows:', len(closest))\n\n# get Al column\nal_col = None\nfor c in clim.columns:\n    if c.strip().lower()=='al' or c.strip().lower().startswith('al'):\n        al_col = c\n        break\nprint('al column detected:', al_col)\nclosest_al = pd.to_numeric(closest[al_col], errors='coerce')\nmax_al = closest_al.max()\nprint('max Al among closest rows:', max_al)\n\n# round to 4 decimals\nout = round(float(max_al),4)\nprint(out)\n\n# also print some diagnostics\nprint('\\nSAMPLE DETAILS:')\nprint(cand[['Region','Site','Layer/Assemblage/Context','Culture','Lab code','date','error','Material','Species',cal2,'Latitude','Longitude']])\nprint('\\nCLOSEST CLIMATE ROWS SAMPLE:')\nprint(closest[[clim_age_col,'Age_BP','Al','diff']].head())\n\n# final output\nprint('\\nFINAL:', out)\n", "dataset_id": "kramabench-archeology-hard-1", "file_path": "files/radiocarbon_database_regional.xlsx"}) [toolUseId=call_FIZYndDwDjoXP